Python offers multiple options for developing a GUI (Graphical User Interface).
Out of all the GUI methods, tkinter is the most commonly used method.
It is a standard Python interface to the Tk GUI toolkit shipped with Python.
Python with tkinter outputs the fastest and easiest way to create GUI applications.
Now, it’s up to the imagination or necessity of a developer, what he/she wants to develop using this
toolkit.

To create a tkinter :



1.Importing the module – tkinter
2.Create the main window (container)
3.Add any number of widgets to the main window.
4.Apply the event Trigger on the widgets.




Let’s create a GUI based simple Age Calculator application that can calculate the age with respect to
the given date and birth date, given by the user.